[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "1. Accepted 5... Bc5"]
[Black "Accepted 5... Bc5 7... dxc3 9... Kf8"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. b4
{ @@HeaderStart@@The Evans Gambit:@@HeaderEnd@@- White sacrifices a pawn for a lead in development, more space, and an attack on the black king    As a principle, White does not want to trade pieces because it diminishes his attacking chances  - In all accepted Evans Gambit variations, we play d4 first and then O-O  - We play Qb3 before O-O if an attack on f7 is hard to defend   Typical ideas:  - ♕b3 with an attack on f7  - ♗a3 with control of the a3-f8 diagonal   - pawn breaks with d4-d5 or e4-e5   Tactical motifs:  - ♗xf7 followed by ♕d5+ with a double attack on Kf7 and Bc5  - after d5 chasing Nc6 away -a double attack with Qa4+ or Qb5+ on Ke8 and Ba5  - chasing and trapping the black queen }
4... Bxb4 5. c3 Bc5
{ On Lichess  (Rapid and Classical games, all ratings)  5... Ba5 and 5... Bc5 are equally popular and played in 35-40% of all the games. Together they cover more than 75% of the games played with the Accepted Evans Gambit.   The move 5... Ba5 is slightly better as after 5... Bc5, White can play d4 and attack the bishop with tempo. }
6. d4 { We play d4 first and later O-O in all variations! } 6... exd4 7. O-O
dxc3 { A common mistake. This allows a double attack. } 8. Bxf7+
{ Not the immediate double attack with  8.Qd5  as  8...Qe7  defends both  Bc5  and pawn  f7  .    White wins 74% of the games versus Black 23% }
8... Kxf7 9. Qd5+ Kf8 10. Qxc5+ d6 11. Qxc3 Qf6
{ Black would like to trade pieces to slow down White's attack. } 12. Qc2 Qxa1
{ Black can not take on  a1  . The queen will be trapped.  Better  12...Nge7  13.Bb2  Qf7  14.Nfd2  followed by  f4  and White is much better.  White can also bring his rook into the attack with a4-Ra3. }
13. Bb2 { Trapping the queen on a1. } 13... Qxa2
{ If  13...Nb4  then  14.Qc3  with a double attack on  g7  and  Nb4  . } 14.
Bxg7+ { A discovered attack on Qa2. } 14... Kxg7 15. Qxa2 { And White wins. } *

