{ 9...c6  10.Bxg8  Rxg8  11.dxe5  dxe5  12.Nxe5±  White is a pawn up and black's king is still unsafe. }
10. Qxa5 exd4 { 10...b6  11.Qa4  Bd7  12.Qc4+  Be6  13.Qe2⩲ } 11. cxd4
{ White has better prospects with control of the center and unsafe black king. Don't trade attackers, especially your queen.   11...Nf6  12.Qb5  Nxe4   12...Rf8  13.Qb3+  d5  14.Nc3  and White has some pull after O-O, Re1, Ne5  13.Qd5++-   An alternative:   11.Qd5+  Be6  12.Qxb7  dxc3  13.Nxc3±  White is better, but the position is very unbalanced. You can play this if you prefer these kinds of positions. }
